# BUGFIX PROTOCOL — BLAST RADIUS CHECK

Before applying any fix, always assess how wide the impact could be.
State the blast radius out loud before touching anything.

## Two Categories

### Narrow Blast Radius
The fix only touches one component's local code — styles, local logic,
text that only lives in that file. Nothing else imports or depends on it.
→ Fix and proceed. Note briefly: "This only affects [file], nothing else uses it."

### Wide Blast Radius
The fix touches a shared file that other parts of the app depend on.
→ Check what imports it first. Name the risk before applying the fix.

Wide blast radius files (always check before changing):
- Any file in `src/store/` (useMasteryStore, useUserStore) — every component that reads store data is affected
- Any file in `src/hooks/` (useResponsiveScale, etc.) — every component using the hook is affected
- `app/_layout.tsx` — controls the root of the entire app, every screen is downstream
- `app/(tabs)/_layout.tsx` — controls all tab screens
- Any shared component in `components/` that is imported by 3+ files

## Format — Say This Before Every Fix

"Blast radius: [narrow/wide] — [one sentence on what is affected and what is not]"

Examples:
- "Blast radius: narrow — this only changes a padding value in index.tsx styles, nothing else imports it."
- "Blast radius: wide — useResponsiveScale is imported by QuestGrid and index.tsx. Checking both before changing."

Never skip this line on a wide blast radius fix.
